  navContact: "Contact",
  titleOverview: "The 304 Connect Project",
  textOverview: "This document presents an investment opportunity in a large 257-rai (approx. 41.12 hectares) plot of land, strategically located in Si Maha Phot District, Prachinburi Province. This land holds outstanding potential for development as a regional industrial hub or logistics center. Key advantages include its single-title deed, simplifying the transaction process; its frontage on National Highway 304, a major logistics artery of the country; and its position within a complete industrial ecosystem, surrounded by leading industrial parks like 304 Industrial Park and Rojana Industrial Park. The property is directly connected to Thailand's critical infrastructure, including the Laem Chabang Deep Sea Port, Suvarnabhumi International Airport, and the land border crossing to Cambodia.\n\nFurthermore, the location benefits from being a gateway to the vast labor pool of Northeastern Thailand and is supported by local technical colleges that continuously produce a skilled workforce. This land is not just a property asset but a gateway to markets in Thailand and the Greater Mekong Subregion (GMS), aligning with government investment promotion policies (BOI) and benefiting from the growth of the Eastern Economic Corridor (EEC). This makes it an exceptionally attractive investment proposal for international investors, especially those from China seeking to establish a strong manufacturing and logistics base in Southeast Asia.",
